The paper deals with the Target Set Selection (TSS) Problem, which is a problem in graph theory and social network analysis. The paper discusses inapproximability and parameterized results for the TSS Problem, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), social and information networks (cs.SI), game theory and economics (cs.GT), computational complexity (cs.CC), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
